Package net.ashwork.functionality.throwable.primitive.shorts

Functions that have specialized short-valued type parameters or return types where a throwable may be thrown.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ThrowingShortFunction1<R>
    Represents a function that accepts a short-valued argument and produces a result or throws a throwable.
    ThrowingShortOperator1
    Represents an operation that accepts a short-valued operand and produces a result of the same type as its operand or throws a throwable.
    ThrowingToShortFunction0
    Represents a function that accepts no arguments and produces a short-valued result or throws a throwable.
    ThrowingToShortFunction1<T1>
    Represents a function that accepts one argument and produces a short-valued result or throws a throwable.
    ThrowingToShortFunction2<T1,T2>
    Represents a function that accepts two arguments and produces a short-valued result or throws a throwable.
    ThrowingToShortFunctionN
    Represents a function that accepts n arguments and produces a short-valued result or throws a throwable.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ThrowingToShortFunctionN.Instance
    An instance of ToShortFunctionN which properly defines the arity of that particular function.

Package net.ashwork.functionality.throwable.primitive.shorts Description
